  "prompt": "What is this new Quora button of a blue human bust with a +?",
  "response": "The blue human bust with a \"+\" on Quora is a feature called **\"Add People to Spaces\"** or **\"Invite to Space.\"** It allows users to invite other people to join a **Space**, which is Quora's feature for hosting live audio conversations or ongoing discussions on specific topics.\n\nHere\u2019s how it works:\n\n1. **Spaces**: Spaces are community-driven areas where people can discuss topics in real-time or asynchronously.\n2. **Invite Button**: The blue human bust with a \"+\" is an invite button. When you click it, you can send an invitation to others to join a specific Space.\n3. **Purpose**: This feature helps Spaces grow by allowing members to bring in new participants who might be interested in the topic.\n\nIf you\u2019re part of a Space, you\u2019ll see this button to help expand the community or invite specific individuals. It\u2019s a way to encourage more engagement and collaboration on Quora.",
